message.content:
Below is one way to “decode” the two target assemblies and match them block‐for‐block (without re‐orienting any dictionary pieces).  First comes a careful breakdown of what is in each structure; then the dictionary‐block selections; finally an example step‐by‐step build order.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1)  ANALYSIS OF THE MAIN TARGET IMAGE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

‣ LEFT‐HAND STRUCTURE
 • Total of 6 blocks.  
 • Layering (from bottom to top):
   1) A short yellow rectangular block as the base.  
   2) A red “U‐shaped” curved block sitting on that base.  
   3) A green rectangular plank bridging across the top of the red block.  
   4) Two separate blue cubes side by side on top of the green plank.  
   5) An orange wedge piece attached at the rear (the “tail”).  

‣ RIGHT‐HAND “WINDOW” STRUCTURE
 • Total of 6 blocks.  
 • Layering:
   1) A long yellow rectangular block on the bottom.  
   2) Two vertical “columns” of cubes in the middle:  
      – Left column: orange cube (bottom), green cube (top)  
      – Right column: red cube (bottom), blue cube (top)  
   3) A second long yellow rectangular block on top, spanning both columns.  

Hence the entire scene uses 12 blocks total (6 in each sub‐assembly), arranged in 3–4 layers depending on how you group them.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2)  MATCHING TO THE DICTIONARY (NO ROTATIONS ALLOWED)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Below are the block‐index picks that match color, shape, **and** orientation exactly as they appear in the dictionary images:

■  LEFT STRUCTURE
  – Base (short yellow plank) → index #13  
  – Red curved “U” block → index #2  
  – Green rectangular plank (horizontal orientation) → index #9  
  – Two blue cubes → index #5 (used twice)  
  – Orange wedge piece → index #15  

■  RIGHT STRUCTURE
  – Bottom yellow bar (long) → index #12  
  – Top yellow bar (long) → index #12 again  
  – Orange cube → index #7  
  – Green cube → index #6  
  – Red cube → index #8  
  – Blue cube → index #5  

Note that block‐indices #5, #12, etc. may be reused multiple times as needed.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3)  STEP‐BY‐STEP ASSEMBLY INSTRUCTIONS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

{
  Step1: Move block with index 13         // Short yellow base (left side)
  Step2: Move block with index 2          // Red “U” shaped block on top
  Step3: Move block with index 9          // Green plank bridging the red piece
  Step4: Move block with index 5          // First blue cube on top
  Step5: Move block with index 5          // Second blue cube alongside the first
  Step6: Move block with index 15         // Orange wedge (tail) on the left structure
  
  // Now build the right-hand "window"
  Step7: Move block with index 12         // Long yellow bar (bottom)
  Step8: Move block with index 7          // Orange cube (left column, bottom)
  Step9: Move block with index 6          // Green cube (left column, top)
  Step10: Move block with index 8         // Red cube (right column, bottom)
  Step11: Move block with index 5         // Blue cube (right column, top)
  Step12: Move block with index 12        // Long yellow bar (top) 
}

This sequence places each dictionary part in the order needed to re‐create the target layout exactly as shown.
